race.comment: IVY DEXSTRESS (6) may have suffered from the dreaded second-up syndrome last time out but go on the solid Doomben win when resuming. Has won two of three over this six-furlong journey and should be right there when the judge calls a halt. CUTEPI (3) will be ready to peak now fourth run in and maps ideally for hoop Mallyon from gate two. Has only missed a drum once in four attempts over this trip and looms as the main danger. HURRICANE LU (7) hasn't done much wrong winning both starts in lesser grade and has earned her shot at this company now. Could easily bring up the hat-trick. The well-related ANARITA (9) (full to G2 winner Kristilli) has hit the top-five in eight of her past nine outings and doesn't know how to put in a poor one. Has to be included in calculations.
